thanks</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 17:32:58 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2170/how-to-change-ctrlaltfn-shortcuts/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by joepd for &lt;p&gt;hi everyone&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I want to change the default &lt;code&gt;ctrl+alt+f1&lt;/code&gt; shortcut to mod4+`  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but &lt;code&gt;chvt&lt;/code&gt; command won't work without &lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I'm using debian, any Idea ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2170/how-to-change-ctrlaltfn-shortcuts/?answer=2171#post-id-2171</link><description>You could make the `chvt` command passwordless in `/etc/sudoers`. 

edit:
Or if you (are|need to be) security conscious, use [`gksudo`](https://faq.i3wm.org/question/123/automatic-question-for-root) in stead of `sudo`. </description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 17:44:32 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2170/how-to-change-ctrlaltfn-shortcuts/?answer=2171#post-id-2171</guid></item><item><title>Comment by raoof for &lt;p&gt;You could make the &lt;code&gt;chvt&lt;/code&gt; command passwordless in &lt;code&gt;/etc/sudoers&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;edit:
Or if you (are|need to be) security conscious, use &lt;a href="https://faq.i3wm.org/question/123/automatic-question-for-root"&gt;&lt;code&gt;gksudo&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in stead of &lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
